This paper deals with approximate pattern matching, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of bidirectional text indexes suggests that the paper may belong to the data structures (cs.DS) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the development of a formalism and probabilistic measure suggests that the paper may also belong to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) or computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories. Finally, the experimental computations suggest that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
